# DayForge

Goal-to-task productivity app. React + Vite + Supabase.

## Conventions

- Use `supabase` from `src/lib/supabaseClient.ts` — never instantiate a second client
- All user data queries must filter by `user_id` (or `profiles.id = auth user id`)
- Auth state via `useAuth()` hook in `src/lib/hooks/useAuth.ts`
- Styling: CSS variables in `index.css`, `glass-panel` class, inline styles for layout (existing pattern)
- Icons: `lucide-react`

## Data tables

`profiles`, `goals`, `tasks`, `notifications` — see `PROJECT.md` and `supabase/migrations/`

## Before adding features

1. Check `PROJECT.md` feature status
2. Add RLS-safe queries (`.eq('user_id', user.id)`)
3. Update `PROJECT.md` when completing a milestone
